      "message": "Maybe we should promote this to `void Fuzz::next(std::string*)`?\n\nOne other thing I\u0027ve just remembered: as written everything looks fine, but we don\u0027t usually have things that interact with Fuzz return the result.  Instead we tend to use an out-parameter, as returning the value makes it easy to become sensitive to function argument evaluation order.  E.g. foo(make_fuzz_string(fuzz), make_fuzz_string(fuzz)) can evaluate in two orders, and does depending on the compiler.)",
